title: US military jet crashes resulting in fatality
text:
Click here for information and nomination US military jet crashes resulting in fatality 
A recent report confirms the crashing of a US military jet F-18 on farm land in Redmere, near a British air base. 
The event happened today, October 21 and alarm was raised by a member of the public at 10.30 am. 
A statement from US officials (confirmed by Cambridgeshire Police) says the pilot, the only crew member, had died. 
The aircraft had taken off from the Lakenheath air base in eastern England, but had no connection to the base. 
The U.S. Embassy in London provided the details on the plane model, which was a supersonic F-18. The Air Force stated investigation into the crash had been started. By Polina Davydova | Oct 21, 2015
